1
00:00:00,340 --> 00:00:01,840
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:01,840 --> 00:00:03,380
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:03,440 --> 00:00:05,210
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:11,880 --> 00:00:14,490
So what is it that you want from me?

5
00:00:15,390 --> 00:00:17,590
Am I supposed to take her place,
letting you hold me,

6
00:00:18,590 --> 00:00:19,960
and holding you in return?

7
00:00:23,230 --> 00:00:25,400
Does that really justify
avoiding it?

8
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:29,030
Are you avoiding fights because
you think there's no point...

9
00:00:29,300 --> 00:00:30,600
in living without her?

10
00:00:31,240 --> 00:00:33,410
Could you actually tell her that...

11
00:00:33,740 --> 00:00:35,570
with a straight face?

12
00:00:36,840 --> 00:00:39,710
It's your choice
whether you have the wedding or not,

13
00:00:40,150 --> 00:00:42,310
but you should ask yourself
if it's a cowardly...

14
00:00:43,520 --> 00:00:44,680
and shameful one.

15
00:01:09,540 --> 00:01:11,080
(Episode 20)

16
00:01:15,410 --> 00:01:16,850
Is he still not picking up?

17
00:01:18,950 --> 00:01:19,950
I'm afraid so.

18
00:01:20,850 --> 00:01:22,890
He really needs to be here on time.

19
00:01:23,290 --> 00:01:25,220
You texted him.

20
00:01:25,590 --> 00:01:26,960
He'll come as soon as he sees it.

21
00:01:33,670 --> 00:01:35,270
It looks like Min Jun
is running a little late.

22
00:01:35,570 --> 00:01:36,870
Please have some tea while we wait.

23
00:01:39,200 --> 00:01:43,110
We're setting a wedding date today,
no matter what.

24
00:01:43,310 --> 00:01:46,140
I'll wait all night for him
if I have to.

25
00:01:49,650 --> 00:01:50,680
Goodness!

26
00:01:51,120 --> 00:01:52,150
Min Jun.

27
00:01:52,350 --> 00:01:54,320
Min Jun, you're here.

28
00:01:54,590 --> 00:01:57,690
Finally, we get to sit down
and chat today.

29
00:01:58,390 --> 00:02:00,530
Come on now, plop yourself down.

30
00:02:00,660 --> 00:02:03,560
I mean, please take a seat.

31
00:02:04,960 --> 00:02:07,630
Let's set our wedding date
before we eat.

32
00:02:12,170 --> 00:02:14,910
Don't just stand there, sit down.

33
00:02:21,010 --> 00:02:22,080
I'm sorry,

34
00:02:22,750 --> 00:02:24,180
but I have to call off...

35
00:02:25,020 --> 00:02:26,220
the wedding.

36
00:02:33,660 --> 00:02:34,660
What?

37
00:02:51,940 --> 00:02:54,910
I wanted to ruin the wedding
Yu Na wanted so badly,

38
00:02:55,510 --> 00:02:59,320
so I used Hyun Jun
and even you, Min Jun.

39
00:03:00,950 --> 00:03:03,760
A part of me wanted you
to call off the wedding,

40
00:03:04,560 --> 00:03:08,290
but I'm worried about everything
you'll have to face.

41
00:03:09,530 --> 00:03:10,630
I'm such a fool.

42
00:03:21,210 --> 00:03:22,210
Min Jun.

43
00:03:22,810 --> 00:03:25,510
- Let's talk first.
- Mother,

44
00:03:25,840 --> 00:03:27,880
I don't want to go through
with this marriage.

45
00:03:28,480 --> 00:03:29,480
I'm sorry.

46
00:03:36,750 --> 00:03:37,860
My goodness!

47
00:03:38,660 --> 00:03:39,760
Ms. Choi!

48
00:03:40,660 --> 00:03:42,490
Who do you think
you're laying a hand on?

49
00:03:44,030 --> 00:03:48,700
You're one to talk.
Who are you to touch my daughter?

50
00:03:48,930 --> 00:03:51,270
Your son
just called off the wedding.

51
00:03:51,270 --> 00:03:53,400
Do you think a slap is enough?

52
00:03:58,140 --> 00:03:59,840
I won't back down.

53
00:03:59,840 --> 00:04:01,950
Do you know what I had to do
to make this wedding happen?

54
00:04:02,010 --> 00:04:03,580
To have you, I...

55
00:04:03,580 --> 00:04:06,080
- Quiet!
- My goodness.

56
00:04:06,150 --> 00:04:07,250
Unbelievable.

57
00:04:10,250 --> 00:04:11,460
My gosh.

58
00:04:13,560 --> 00:04:16,690
How dare you cause a scene
in my house?

59
00:04:16,690 --> 00:04:18,200
Then,

60
00:04:18,530 --> 00:04:20,330
sort this out right now.

61
00:04:21,370 --> 00:04:24,970
I won't back down from this.
You know why.

62
00:04:26,140 --> 00:04:29,610
You personally promised me
a place by Min Jun's side.

63
00:04:30,040 --> 00:04:31,140
Quiet!

64
00:04:33,310 --> 00:04:34,310
Kim Myung Hui.

65
00:04:35,450 --> 00:04:36,450
Yes, sir.

66
00:04:37,920 --> 00:04:41,220
Get this situation under control.
And you!

67
00:04:42,650 --> 00:04:43,860
Come with me.

68
00:04:49,730 --> 00:04:52,460
- Min Jun.
- I was prepared for this.

69
00:04:53,530 --> 00:04:54,700
I can handle it.

70
00:05:04,610 --> 00:05:05,880
You should get going for now.

71
00:05:06,910 --> 00:05:08,880
Even after all that,
you still won't take my side.

72
00:05:10,280 --> 00:05:11,980
Now that you're president at Adele,

73
00:05:11,980 --> 00:05:14,650
you don't need him to marry me
for my family's shares anymore.

74
00:05:14,890 --> 00:05:16,650
I understand that you're angry,

75
00:05:17,690 --> 00:05:19,490
but don't stoop this low.

76
00:05:20,830 --> 00:05:23,030
Who are you saying stooped low here?

77
00:05:24,560 --> 00:05:28,900
Unbelievable.
I really tried to be civil,

78
00:05:28,970 --> 00:05:30,440
but this is just wrong.

79
00:05:30,440 --> 00:05:32,670
Who upset her enough...

80
00:05:32,740 --> 00:05:34,940
to bring out her ugly side?

81
00:05:35,610 --> 00:05:40,140
That's right.
We won't take this anymore.

82
00:05:41,110 --> 00:05:43,780
Honey, say your piece too.

83
00:05:44,080 --> 00:05:45,220
Honey?

84
00:05:45,950 --> 00:05:46,950
Honey?

85
00:05:47,150 --> 00:05:49,150
Where did he go? What?

86
00:05:50,290 --> 00:05:51,520
What are you doing over there?

87
00:05:52,320 --> 00:05:53,560
Things got scary.

88
00:05:58,300 --> 00:06:00,900
Let's not stick around
and risk his wrath.

89
00:06:02,130 --> 00:06:03,330
We should get out of here.

90
00:06:07,340 --> 00:06:08,340
Yu Na!

91
00:06:11,140 --> 00:06:12,240
Yu Na!

92
00:06:26,090 --> 00:06:27,090
What's your reason?

93
00:06:28,230 --> 00:06:30,500
It was never a wedding you wanted.

94
00:06:30,760 --> 00:06:33,630
You told me to do whatever I wanted,
that you didn't care.

95
00:06:34,830 --> 00:06:36,730
So why are you backing out now?

96
00:06:37,640 --> 00:06:38,840
Because I'm ashamed.

97
00:06:40,270 --> 00:06:41,270
What?

98
00:06:42,340 --> 00:06:46,140
Honestly,
I thought my life was already over.

99
00:06:46,380 --> 00:06:49,810
Instead of living my own life,
I was ready to let...

100
00:06:50,110 --> 00:06:51,980
you or Mother control it.

101
00:06:53,620 --> 00:06:54,620
But now...

102
00:06:55,350 --> 00:06:59,060
I'm ashamed of living a life
I'd already given up on.

103
00:07:00,460 --> 00:07:02,860
From now on, I'm taking it back...

104
00:07:05,700 --> 00:07:07,630
and living on my own terms.

105
00:07:09,330 --> 00:07:10,600
On your own terms?

106
00:07:12,070 --> 00:07:15,170
Everything you have came from me.

107
00:07:16,710 --> 00:07:19,010
What gives you the right to say
you'll live as you please?

108
00:07:19,080 --> 00:07:20,550
Then take it all back.

109
00:07:21,150 --> 00:07:24,480
There's nothing you've given me
that I ever wanted.

110
00:07:25,680 --> 00:07:26,820
What did you just say?

111
00:07:28,220 --> 00:07:31,560
- You insolent little punk!
- Sir!

112
00:07:34,530 --> 00:07:35,590
What happened today...

113
00:07:36,430 --> 00:07:38,130
is all my fault.

114
00:07:40,500 --> 00:07:41,970
Please, just give Min Jun...

115
00:07:42,800 --> 00:07:44,970
Just give us a little more time.

116
00:07:52,440 --> 00:07:54,550
I can't stand the sight of you two.
Get out!

117
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:17,130
What in the world is all this?

118
00:08:17,970 --> 00:08:20,500
Was this a family gathering
or a brawl?

119
00:08:20,910 --> 00:08:25,380
This must've ended
with someone getting a black eye.

120
00:08:29,010 --> 00:08:31,680
Mrs. Ok!

121
00:08:40,020 --> 00:08:43,190
Are you that happy
the family gathering was a bust?

122
00:08:43,590 --> 00:08:44,760
Why shouldn't I be?

123
00:08:45,500 --> 00:08:47,160
Had I known,
I would've come early...

124
00:08:47,160 --> 00:08:49,430
just to see that witch Kim Myung Hui
turn pale...

125
00:08:49,500 --> 00:08:51,100
with my own eyes.

126
00:08:53,240 --> 00:08:54,240
The sweet taste of victory.

127
00:08:54,940 --> 00:08:57,710
I'm savoring every little moment.

128
00:08:57,710 --> 00:08:59,640
It's so good, I could just die.

129
00:09:01,810 --> 00:09:05,120
If it's so good,
why don't you have some?

130
00:09:05,950 --> 00:09:09,050
Who do you think you're serving
this cold food to?

131
00:09:09,190 --> 00:09:12,960
If you're not going to eat,
please step aside.

132
00:09:13,460 --> 00:09:15,830
I'll clear the table.

133
00:09:16,230 --> 00:09:17,760
No, stop right there.

134
00:09:18,160 --> 00:09:19,630
Who gave you permission
to clear the table?

135
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:22,270
You said you weren't going to eat.

136
00:09:22,630 --> 00:09:25,140
Leave it for that witch
to come and see.

137
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:27,370
The family gathering
and her son's wedding...

138
00:09:27,370 --> 00:09:28,710
have both turned sour.

139
00:09:29,140 --> 00:09:32,310
The feast went south
before anyone could even eat.

140
00:09:32,480 --> 00:09:34,150
I want it to really sink in for her.

141
00:09:34,450 --> 00:09:36,250
I can't believe you.

142
00:09:38,980 --> 00:09:40,250
You're a real piece of work, ma'am.

143
00:09:41,020 --> 00:09:42,020
What was that?

144
00:09:43,750 --> 00:09:47,260
You know what? I'm not going
to let you ruin my good mood.

145
00:09:48,360 --> 00:09:51,060
Mrs. Ok, it's your lucky day.

146
00:09:51,130 --> 00:09:54,930
This disaster put me in a good mood,
so you get a pass.

147
00:09:55,430 --> 00:09:57,870
- Understand?
- What disaster?

148
00:10:00,240 --> 00:10:01,810
My son!

149
00:10:02,310 --> 00:10:05,680
I knew you were born lucky.

150
00:10:06,310 --> 00:10:08,910
Hyun Jun, you don't need
to worry anymore.

151
00:10:09,210 --> 00:10:13,350
All it takes is one lucky break,
and their plans went up in smoke.

152
00:10:14,590 --> 00:10:16,090
But I don't see any smoke.

153
00:10:16,450 --> 00:10:19,220
She means
the family gathering fell through.

154
00:10:19,890 --> 00:10:21,260
Wait, again?

155
00:10:21,860 --> 00:10:23,530
- Why?
- Well...

156
00:10:23,590 --> 00:10:24,600
Ta-da!

157
00:10:25,530 --> 00:10:28,700
That punk Park Min Jun
called the whole thing off himself.

158
00:10:29,570 --> 00:10:31,100
He actually said that?

159
00:10:48,590 --> 00:10:51,720
I'm sorry for ruining your plan.

160
00:10:58,200 --> 00:10:59,630
Outside the study,

161
00:11:00,900 --> 00:11:02,830
I heard you talking to the chairman.

162
00:11:04,940 --> 00:11:07,000
You said you'd given up
on your own life,

163
00:11:09,070 --> 00:11:11,340
and that you were just going
to let us control you.

164
00:11:12,540 --> 00:11:15,350
Is that how you've been feeling
this whole time?

165
00:11:15,880 --> 00:11:17,820
Is this how it's been
ever since I stopped you...

166
00:11:18,580 --> 00:11:19,780
from studying abroad?

167
00:11:20,750 --> 00:11:22,490
It wasn't just because of you.

168
00:11:23,020 --> 00:11:25,590
The woman I loved died,

169
00:11:27,460 --> 00:11:28,790
so I gave up on everything.

170
00:11:30,030 --> 00:11:31,400
The person you loved?

171
00:11:32,430 --> 00:11:35,200
You mean the girlfriend
you were going to study abroad with?

172
00:11:37,300 --> 00:11:40,740
The one I mistook for Ms. Choi?

173
00:11:40,970 --> 00:11:42,740
Was it that hard on you,

174
00:11:43,370 --> 00:11:44,780
not being able to leave with her?

175
00:11:47,310 --> 00:11:49,580
I never even got to say I was sorry
before I lost her.

176
00:11:51,050 --> 00:11:54,450
I never thought I'd lose her
so suddenly and so painfully.

177
00:11:57,350 --> 00:11:59,590
She must've suffered so much
in those flames...

178
00:12:03,430 --> 00:12:05,660
Thinking about it
makes it hard to breathe.

179
00:12:07,200 --> 00:12:08,600
Flames?

180
00:12:11,840 --> 00:12:12,970
There was an accident.

181
00:12:15,110 --> 00:12:17,980
Actually, no. It wasn't an accident.

182
00:12:18,310 --> 00:12:20,280
She was robbed of her life...

183
00:12:20,280 --> 00:12:22,450
because her father decided
to end both their lives.

184
00:12:23,750 --> 00:12:24,820
What do you mean?

185
00:12:26,050 --> 00:12:30,050
When Father took over Temi Bio,
there was a car explosion.

186
00:12:30,550 --> 00:12:33,920
Do you remember Baek Jun Gi,
who killed himself and his daughter?

187
00:12:35,930 --> 00:12:37,660
The woman I loved, Jin Ju,

188
00:12:38,730 --> 00:12:40,600
was the daughter of Baek Jun Gi,

189
00:12:41,330 --> 00:12:42,530
the CEO of Temi Bio.

190
00:12:53,410 --> 00:12:54,780
She...

191
00:12:55,450 --> 00:12:57,350
It's a healthy baby boy.

192
00:12:57,980 --> 00:13:00,050
It's a miracle, plain and simple.

193
00:13:00,450 --> 00:13:03,350
Doctor,
your daughter is healthy too.

194
00:13:03,850 --> 00:13:04,960
Both babies...

195
00:13:05,490 --> 00:13:07,760
were born the same day,
at the exact same time.

196
00:13:08,560 --> 00:13:09,660
How...

197
00:13:10,430 --> 00:13:11,960
How could the two of you...

198
00:13:14,100 --> 00:13:16,500
I knew she was the one
the moment I met her.

199
00:13:41,630 --> 00:13:43,890
Every moment I spent with Jin Ju...

200
00:13:45,600 --> 00:13:47,800
was the first time
I ever felt true warmth...

201
00:13:49,530 --> 00:13:50,730
and happiness.

202
00:14:11,590 --> 00:14:14,360
I never imagined I'd lose her
in such a cruel, unfair way.

203
00:14:16,690 --> 00:14:18,960
I never knew
it would leave a scar...

204
00:14:20,700 --> 00:14:22,700
that would never heal.

205
00:14:26,540 --> 00:14:28,610
(Hanbit High School
62nd Graduation Ceremony)

206
00:14:29,110 --> 00:14:30,170
Dad.

207
00:14:48,960 --> 00:14:50,660
Of all people...

208
00:15:01,110 --> 00:15:03,210
Sorry to call so late,

209
00:15:03,410 --> 00:15:05,340
but I need your help
with something urgent.

210
00:15:06,380 --> 00:15:07,540
This is about Temi Bio.

211
00:15:08,750 --> 00:15:11,050
Find out everything you can
about Dr. Baek's daughter.

212
00:15:15,620 --> 00:15:16,950
Park Min Jun!

213
00:15:18,720 --> 00:15:20,920
Why now, after everything?

214
00:15:24,630 --> 00:15:25,630
Meaning...

215
00:15:25,630 --> 00:15:28,970
I might just steal something
from you too.

216
00:15:30,070 --> 00:15:31,400
For example,

217
00:15:32,170 --> 00:15:34,140
Park Min Jun.

218
00:15:36,910 --> 00:15:39,280
Fine. Go ahead and marry him.

219
00:15:39,640 --> 00:15:42,210
That won't stop me
from having fun with him.

220
00:15:44,210 --> 00:15:45,220
That's it.

221
00:15:46,150 --> 00:15:49,620
Ever since Chloe showed up,
Min Jun and his mom have changed.

222
00:15:51,320 --> 00:15:53,490
I need to remove Chloe from Adele
for good.

223
00:15:57,830 --> 00:15:58,830
But how?

224
00:16:00,060 --> 00:16:01,100
What can I possibly do?

225
00:16:03,700 --> 00:16:04,700
Think.

226
00:16:06,970 --> 00:16:08,170
I have to think of something.

227
00:16:17,210 --> 00:16:18,420
Hey, over here.

228
00:16:20,920 --> 00:16:22,950
What about what I asked for?

229
00:16:22,950 --> 00:16:25,020
You think I'd come empty-handed?

230
00:16:26,590 --> 00:16:29,460
I found out which school
Baek Jin Ju went to...

231
00:16:29,530 --> 00:16:32,100
and looked through
all their yearbooks.

232
00:16:32,400 --> 00:16:33,530
I even found a picture of her.

233
00:16:34,530 --> 00:16:35,530
Nicely done.

234
00:16:36,400 --> 00:16:37,500
Right,

235
00:16:37,700 --> 00:16:39,470
- but something here is weird.
- How so?

236
00:16:39,470 --> 00:16:40,740
Check out her photo.

237
00:16:40,900 --> 00:16:41,970
Her photo?

238
00:16:44,270 --> 00:16:46,210
(Personal Profile)

239
00:16:48,450 --> 00:16:50,350
(Hanbit High School
62nd Graduation Ceremony)

240
00:16:51,980 --> 00:16:54,180
See? It's weird, right?
It's not just me.

241
00:16:54,650 --> 00:16:58,320
Hey, go on ahead. I've got to run.

242
00:17:06,460 --> 00:17:09,330
Is this what you found
on Dr. Baek's daughter?

243
00:17:09,600 --> 00:17:10,600
Yes,

244
00:17:10,970 --> 00:17:12,740
but here's the thing.

245
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:16,070
Just brace yourself.

246
00:17:17,810 --> 00:17:21,110
Dr. Baek's daughter and Min Jun
were dating.

247
00:17:21,550 --> 00:17:23,310
What could be more shocking
than that?

248
00:17:24,280 --> 00:17:25,280
Tell me about it.

249
00:17:25,880 --> 00:17:28,950
But believe me, there's something
even more unbelievable.

250
00:18:07,290 --> 00:18:08,290
Good morning.

251
00:18:09,160 --> 00:18:10,430
It's a beautiful morning.

252
00:18:13,560 --> 00:18:15,270
For me, it's a brand new day.

253
00:18:16,400 --> 00:18:17,730
A brand new day?

254
00:18:18,670 --> 00:18:21,170
I called off the wedding.

255
00:18:23,140 --> 00:18:25,780
I've decided to stop running away...

256
00:18:27,410 --> 00:18:28,680
and live my own life.

257
00:18:30,180 --> 00:18:31,250
It's all thanks to you.

258
00:18:34,280 --> 00:18:35,320
Really?

259
00:18:36,690 --> 00:18:38,390
I'm not sure
if I should congratulate you...

260
00:18:38,690 --> 00:18:40,360
or say I'm sorry.

261
00:18:41,630 --> 00:18:43,760
Either way, I'm rooting for you.

262
00:19:18,660 --> 00:19:20,130
I hear you caused
quite a scene yesterday.

263
00:19:21,230 --> 00:19:22,900
It wasn't as bad as I expected.

264
00:19:23,930 --> 00:19:26,370
Knowing Chairman Park's temper,

265
00:19:26,370 --> 00:19:28,610
the fact that you're still
in one piece...

266
00:19:30,010 --> 00:19:31,910
means your mother
must've taken your side.

267
00:19:33,080 --> 00:19:34,410
Or is he actually okay with you...

268
00:19:35,180 --> 00:19:36,450
calling off the wedding?

269
00:19:38,480 --> 00:19:40,650
I explained to my mother
why I couldn't get married.

270
00:19:44,450 --> 00:19:47,020
I told her everything,
from the accident to Jin Ju.

271
00:19:52,760 --> 00:19:54,430
Sir, we have a major problem.

272
00:19:59,070 --> 00:20:00,170
- An official statement...
- That's absolutely...

273
00:20:00,170 --> 00:20:01,240
- will be released shortly.
- not true.

274
00:20:01,240 --> 00:20:02,970
We're still looking into it.

275
00:20:04,810 --> 00:20:06,540
- About the design being stolen?
- What?

276
00:20:06,740 --> 00:20:07,740
- Absolutely not.
- The accusation...

277
00:20:07,810 --> 00:20:09,250
is completely false.

278
00:20:09,250 --> 00:20:10,680
At BIT Life,

279
00:20:10,880 --> 00:20:13,080
we prioritize design ethics
above all else.

280
00:20:15,120 --> 00:20:16,620
Those reports are pure speculation.

281
00:20:19,120 --> 00:20:22,630
This is BIT Life's new symbol.

282
00:20:24,190 --> 00:20:26,900
This is my design.

283
00:20:28,400 --> 00:20:29,530
Now, take a look.

284
00:20:31,770 --> 00:20:33,140
This is plagiarism.

285
00:20:35,040 --> 00:20:36,640
Adele Group's bio division.

286
00:20:37,240 --> 00:20:39,080
The new BIT Life symbol.

287
00:20:39,080 --> 00:20:41,750
They stole it from me,
just an unknown designer.

288
00:20:42,980 --> 00:20:45,680
Isn't it identical to the design
in this design book?

289
00:20:45,980 --> 00:20:47,450
I can't believe someone...

290
00:21:00,260 --> 00:21:01,430
My design book...

291
00:21:02,430 --> 00:21:03,570
is gone.

292
00:21:11,270 --> 00:21:12,980
How could you let this happen?

293
00:21:13,210 --> 00:21:15,550
Those are false accusations
and slander.

294
00:21:15,610 --> 00:21:18,080
He had his actual design book
with him.

295
00:21:18,320 --> 00:21:19,320
Are you saying he's lying?

296
00:21:19,420 --> 00:21:22,390
He could've seen our symbol
and copied it.

297
00:21:22,450 --> 00:21:23,820
Whether it's true or not,

298
00:21:25,790 --> 00:21:27,920
how are you going to answer
for these damages?

299
00:21:28,290 --> 00:21:32,160
Our image has been ruined
before the rebranding is even done!

300
00:21:32,900 --> 00:21:36,230
I will find the accuser
and bring the truth to light.

301
00:21:37,970 --> 00:21:40,170
If you don't handle this properly,

302
00:21:40,500 --> 00:21:42,010
you'll be fired as president...

303
00:21:42,470 --> 00:21:44,680
and completely cut off
from the company.

304
00:21:45,310 --> 00:21:47,540
Mark my words. Manager Kang.

305
00:21:51,650 --> 00:21:52,680
Yes, sir.

306
00:21:52,880 --> 00:21:57,050
Have the legal team
use any means to fight this.

307
00:21:57,150 --> 00:21:58,160
No,

308
00:21:58,160 --> 00:22:01,320
have them find the fastest solution
and bring it to me!

309
00:22:01,320 --> 00:22:02,460
Yes, sir.

310
00:22:03,690 --> 00:22:05,700
(Chairman Park Tae Ho)

311
00:22:08,330 --> 00:22:09,330
Darn it.

312
00:22:12,540 --> 00:22:14,440
(Consultant, Chloe Lee)

313
00:22:17,370 --> 00:22:18,380
Yes?

314
00:22:19,040 --> 00:22:21,410
I'm not in charge of the design,
so I wouldn't know.

315
00:22:22,780 --> 00:22:25,080
Gosh, you can't be serious.

316
00:22:26,680 --> 00:22:28,220
Why would
a genius consultant like her...

317
00:22:28,650 --> 00:22:31,020
do something that shameless?

318
00:22:36,560 --> 00:22:37,560
Sure.

319
00:22:47,700 --> 00:22:48,710
Hey.

320
00:22:49,640 --> 00:22:51,410
Did you look into it?

321
00:22:51,480 --> 00:22:53,610
I have people trying to identify
the man in the video.

322
00:22:54,340 --> 00:22:55,650
That won't be enough.

323
00:22:59,620 --> 00:23:01,520
The design book he showed
on the livestream.

324
00:23:02,350 --> 00:23:03,750
That's where we should start.

325
00:23:04,590 --> 00:23:06,190
That's actually mine.

326
00:23:06,520 --> 00:23:08,160
It’s the only thing missing
from my desk.

327
00:23:09,290 --> 00:23:13,060
Then the first thing we need to do
is prove the design book was stolen.

328
00:23:14,970 --> 00:23:16,970
Father, focus on tracking down
the person from the livestream.

329
00:23:17,230 --> 00:23:20,300
We'll look into
how the design book went missing.

330
00:23:20,700 --> 00:23:22,040
All right.

331
00:23:23,140 --> 00:23:25,340
Please take care of Chloe.

332
00:23:26,180 --> 00:23:27,340
Don't worry.

333
00:23:28,550 --> 00:23:31,050
Let's go check the office again.

334
00:23:31,650 --> 00:23:32,680
Okay.

335
00:23:33,150 --> 00:23:35,690
- We'll get going.
- All right, be careful.

336
00:23:36,450 --> 00:23:37,450
Sure.

337
00:23:46,360 --> 00:23:48,600
(Break Room)

338
00:23:53,070 --> 00:23:54,300
You seem to be in a good mood.

339
00:23:56,510 --> 00:23:57,610
What's it to you?

340
00:23:58,310 --> 00:23:59,440
Mind your own business.

341
00:24:00,510 --> 00:24:03,510
Yesterday,
your wedding plans went up in smoke,

342
00:24:03,580 --> 00:24:06,850
and today, this massive scandal
hits the company.

343
00:24:07,050 --> 00:24:09,490
Yet you look happy,
which makes me curious.

344
00:24:11,220 --> 00:24:12,760
Or rather, suspicious.

345
00:24:14,890 --> 00:24:17,230
No one's taking my wedding away,

346
00:24:17,860 --> 00:24:19,760
and this company mess
has nothing to do with me.

347
00:24:21,830 --> 00:24:23,770
So why shouldn't I smile?

348
00:24:25,470 --> 00:24:27,840
Go ahead.
Enjoy smiling while you can.

349
00:24:29,470 --> 00:24:30,470
But...

350
00:24:31,580 --> 00:24:33,940
if you had anything to do with this,

351
00:24:34,380 --> 00:24:36,150
if you set the whole thing up,

352
00:24:36,680 --> 00:24:39,380
have you thought about
who'd be the most furious?

353
00:24:40,450 --> 00:24:41,450
Obviously...

354
00:24:41,650 --> 00:24:43,890
Who, Chloe? No, wait.

355
00:24:44,490 --> 00:24:45,590
President Kim?

356
00:24:49,230 --> 00:24:51,160
It would undoubtedly be
Chairman Park.

357
00:24:53,260 --> 00:24:54,260
What?

358
00:24:54,630 --> 00:24:56,130
My father...

359
00:24:56,930 --> 00:25:00,870
never forgives anyone
who tarnishes Adele's reputation.

360
00:25:01,440 --> 00:25:03,810
If they catch the guy
who made that bogus broadcast,

361
00:25:06,280 --> 00:25:07,510
he won't let it slide.

362
00:25:09,310 --> 00:25:13,680
He'll completely crush the accuser,
legally or otherwise.

363
00:25:15,650 --> 00:25:18,960
So you should really think about
whether you can afford that smile.

364
00:25:19,620 --> 00:25:20,620
Got it?

365
00:25:27,060 --> 00:25:30,200
Whatever. There's no way
anyone can prove I did it.

366
00:25:31,470 --> 00:25:33,740
Besides, he said
he'd lay low for a while.

367
00:25:35,810 --> 00:25:37,010
Everything's fine.

368
00:25:44,450 --> 00:25:45,920
Why on earth would someone do this?

369
00:25:47,350 --> 00:25:49,150
Have you looked for the person
who made the broadcast?

370
00:25:49,450 --> 00:25:52,820
He hid his identity,
so he's hard to track down.

371
00:25:53,220 --> 00:25:57,030
The legal team is on it,
so they should identify him soon.

372
00:25:58,030 --> 00:26:00,060
I just hope they catch
whoever did this.

373
00:26:00,500 --> 00:26:04,000
I swear I'll break every bone
in his body.

374
00:26:04,970 --> 00:26:06,870
We just need to find him
as soon as possible.

375
00:26:07,140 --> 00:26:08,170
By the looks of it,

376
00:26:08,170 --> 00:26:11,370
this account has made
false claims before.

377
00:26:11,880 --> 00:26:15,510
They once accused a famous chef
of stealing their recipe,

378
00:26:15,780 --> 00:26:18,350
but they were actually paid
by a competitor...

379
00:26:18,350 --> 00:26:19,680
to make the claim.

380
00:26:20,450 --> 00:26:22,650
They got sued over it
and even went to trial.

381
00:26:22,950 --> 00:26:23,950
Wait a minute.

382
00:26:24,720 --> 00:26:27,320
So they've done this before...

383
00:26:28,060 --> 00:26:29,890
and were sued
for making false claims?

384
00:26:31,060 --> 00:26:32,060
Yes, what about it?

385
00:26:32,600 --> 00:26:33,860
If we use that,

386
00:26:34,760 --> 00:26:36,900
we could get a lead much faster.

387
00:26:38,170 --> 00:26:39,170
Really?

388
00:26:39,840 --> 00:26:41,070
What do you need me to do?

389
00:26:41,840 --> 00:26:43,970
I'll do whatever it takes.
Just say the word.

390
00:26:58,420 --> 00:26:59,890
Gosh, what the...

391
00:27:02,260 --> 00:27:03,290
What?

392
00:27:05,800 --> 00:27:06,800
Are you...

393
00:27:07,360 --> 00:27:08,370
You too?

394
00:27:14,840 --> 00:27:17,740
Hold on. How did you find out
about this place?

395
00:27:20,010 --> 00:27:22,380
Let's just say
I have a lot of money.

396
00:27:22,750 --> 00:27:25,880
With enough money and people,
you can find out anything.

397
00:27:27,850 --> 00:27:28,850
Hush.

398
00:27:30,550 --> 00:27:34,120
- How about you?
- Me? I'm resourceful.

399
00:27:36,030 --> 00:27:38,860
He's been sued before
over a false claim,

400
00:27:39,360 --> 00:27:42,300
so I pleaded with everyone
involved in that case.

401
00:27:43,170 --> 00:27:45,070
When it comes to President Kim,

402
00:27:46,600 --> 00:27:48,270
I'd run myself ragged for her.

403
00:27:50,970 --> 00:27:55,210
So eventually, they "threw out"
a box of documents for me.

404
00:27:56,050 --> 00:27:57,610
I dug through the box and,

405
00:27:58,380 --> 00:28:01,050
sure enough,
found his information and address.

406
00:28:06,920 --> 00:28:07,920
Hush.

407
00:28:09,730 --> 00:28:11,290
That's all you need to know.

408
00:28:11,900 --> 00:28:13,300
But you already told me everything.

409
00:28:17,900 --> 00:28:19,670
You seem to know
how to throw money around,

410
00:28:21,570 --> 00:28:22,770
but can you handle yourself?

411
00:28:24,770 --> 00:28:28,510
Unbelievable. Just as I suspected.

412
00:28:29,810 --> 00:28:30,810
Then,

413
00:28:33,850 --> 00:28:36,520
you'd better stick close to me.

414
00:28:47,730 --> 00:28:48,730
He's going down...

415
00:28:49,630 --> 00:28:51,430
for messing with my boss.

416
00:28:52,100 --> 00:28:53,200
The feeling's mutual.

417
00:28:54,000 --> 00:28:56,540
He dared to drag Chloe's name
through the mud.

418
00:28:59,410 --> 00:29:00,880
- Get him!
- Get him!

419
00:29:00,880 --> 00:29:02,150
What the...

420
00:29:06,420 --> 00:29:08,720
(BIT Life, President Kim Myung Hui)

421
00:29:16,230 --> 00:29:19,760
The legal team came up with
the quickest way to handle this.

422
00:29:21,060 --> 00:29:22,430
Instead of a false accusation,

423
00:29:22,800 --> 00:29:24,630
they're suggesting
we turn it into a real one.

424
00:29:25,440 --> 00:29:26,470
A real one?

425
00:29:27,200 --> 00:29:28,540
Chloe stole that design,

426
00:29:28,540 --> 00:29:30,670
which made Adele Group
an innocent victim.

427
00:29:31,810 --> 00:29:33,780
We pin all the blame...

428
00:29:34,840 --> 00:29:35,950
on Chloe.

429
00:29:36,650 --> 00:29:38,280
Sir, with all due respect...

430
00:29:38,280 --> 00:29:39,320
Besides,

431
00:29:43,220 --> 00:29:45,660
she was disposable from the start.

432
00:29:45,760 --> 00:29:48,090
She got cocky and started
ignoring me, the chairman.

433
00:29:49,530 --> 00:29:51,090
Such an insolent little thing.

434
00:29:53,960 --> 00:29:57,870
This is a chance to show everyone
how ruthless Adele Group can be.

435
00:29:58,400 --> 00:30:00,800
We'll make a scapegoat out of Chloe,

436
00:30:01,800 --> 00:30:03,170
and then just start over.

437
00:30:08,610 --> 00:30:09,610
Why the hesitation?

438
00:30:10,650 --> 00:30:12,580
Will you let this project die...

439
00:30:12,580 --> 00:30:14,450
and get yourself
kicked out of the company?

440
00:30:23,430 --> 00:30:25,400
Don't overthink it.

441
00:30:26,360 --> 00:30:29,700
Make a decision right now.

442
00:31:10,910 --> 00:31:13,840
(Pearl in Red)

443
00:31:14,040 --> 00:31:17,880
Let's ask the police to investigate
and release the CCTV footage.

444
00:31:17,950 --> 00:31:20,250
Whatever it takes,
I want to clear my name.

445
00:31:20,380 --> 00:31:22,320
If you're going to lie,
at least make it believable.

446
00:31:22,450 --> 00:31:24,150
I've reported it to the chairman.

447
00:31:24,150 --> 00:31:25,660
The police will investigate.

448
00:31:25,790 --> 00:31:27,590
You don't seriously suspect Chloe,
do you?

449
00:31:27,720 --> 00:31:29,760
Do you trust Chloe completely?

450
00:31:29,830 --> 00:31:32,360
Chloe's design will be declared
plagiarized, so that's that.

451
00:31:32,430 --> 00:31:35,570
Are you really accusing me
based on a lie like that?

452
00:31:35,730 --> 00:31:37,200
I'll do as you wish, sir.

453
00:31:38,300 --> 00:31:40,300
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
